<SLUG> BC-BBN-DODGERS-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DODGERS' WHITE SIDELINED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MATT McHALE  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The day Eric Young returned to the lineup after
missing four games with a calf strain, the Dodgers learned Devon
White could miss the Chicago Cubs series with a tight right
hamstring.
</P>
<P>
   White left Sunday's 6-4 Dodgers loss to the Florida Marlins
after doubling in the fifth inning. But he first injured his
hamstring tracking down Greg Counsell's drive in the top of the
inning.
</P>
<P>
   ``I won't be playing (tonight), and it might be a few games,''
White said. ``But I wouldn't classify it as serious. We'll know
more before game time.''
</P>
<P>
   The injury comes during one of White's hottest stretches of the
year. He was 5 for 9 in the first two games of the series,
including a two-run single Saturday. He went 2 for 2 Sunday with a
two-run double.
</P>
<P>
   White will be replaced in center by Todd Hollandsworth, who
missed most of April with a strained right hamstring.
</P>
<P>
   Young walked and scored in the first inning but flied out in his
other three at-bats. ``The leg felt fine,'' said Young, who was
held out of Saturday's game as a precaution. ``The extra day really
helped. Now we're ready to go.''
</P>
<P>
   Hot Hundley: Catcher Todd Hundley has to miss games to rest his
surgically repaired right elbow, but it was difficult to sit Sunday
after finally getting hot at the plate. Hundley was batting .141
before going on a seven-game hitting streak that ended Sunday when
he went 0 for 1 as a pinch hitter. During the span, he batted .464
(13 for 28), including 5 for 8 in the first two games of the
series.
</P>
<P>
   ``I leave that decision to (manager) Davey (Johnson),'' Hundley
said. ``If they want to give me some time off because of the elbow,
I understand. What I'm happiest about is that I've made some
adjustments at the plate. I'm not pulling my head out at the
plate.''
</P>
<P>
   Quick Hits: Florida's Preston Wilson, who hit the game-tying
homer, has six this season but isn't starting. He opened the season
in left when Cliff Floyd was injured, but hit just .198. Now he
only plays against the occasional left-hander. He took Dodgers
starter Chan Ho Park deep on a breaking ball. ``You have to go up
there confident he is going to make a mistake,'' he said. ``I'm not
worried about him throwing off speed, just hard stuff. I was
surprised.''... Gary Sheffield's fifth-inning stolen base was his
fifth and the 45th by the club. The Dodgers are on pace to steal
235 bases this season, 37 more than the Dodgers record of 198, set
in 1962.... The Marlins were 0-9 on weekends, 0-4 on Sunday. The
Dodgers are 0-3 on Sunday with one rainout.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
